caller_intent: Steve wants to evaluate the cost impact of replacing his Volvo with a Colorado in his insurance policy and adjusting coverage (full coverage on the Colorado, removing liability from the Volvo) to determine if it's cheaper than his son having his own policy.
resolution_steps: Agent confirms Steve's intent to replace the Volvo with the Colorado and adjust coverage.
Agent clarifies details: Colorado will have full coverage, Volvo will have liability removed.
Agent agrees to run the numbers and provide a cost comparison.
Agent commits to calling back with results.
knowledge_required: Understanding of insurance policy structures (coverage types, vehicle additions/removals)
Ability to calculate premium changes based on vehicle and coverage adjustments
summary: Steve is considering replacing his Volvo with a Colorado and adjusting coverage to reduce costs. The agent will analyze the policy changes and provide a cost comparison. The call ends with the agent promising to follow up with results.
